parse.title: List of countries by grape production

text.*:
Countries by grape production in 2016

This is a list of countries by grape production in 2016, based on data from the Food and Agriculture Organization Corporate Statistical Database.[1] The total world production for grapes in 2016 was 77,438,929 metric tonnes. China was the largest producer of grapes, accounting for 19.1% of global production. Italy came second at 10.6%, followed by the United States at 9.2%.
